com.camerontec.catalys.core.message

Class MessageException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • com.camerontec.catalys.core.exception.CatalysException
          • com.camerontec.catalys.core.message.MessageException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    InboundValidationException, ValidationException

    public class MessageException
extends CatalysException
    Indicates that a problem was detected with the content or format of a Message.

    For example, a message is missing a required field.

    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Constructor Detail

      • MessageException

        public MessageException(int code,
                        String s,
                        Object data,
                        Throwable nested,
                        String msgSeqNum,
                        String msgType,
                        int tagID)
        This constructor allows you to associate a number of extra message values with the message exception.

        These extra values are those commonly used in the FIX Session level Reject message. Often a MessageException will result in the sending of a Reject message containing these values.

        Parameters:
        code - Indicates the cause of the message exception.
        s - Any text associated with the exception.
        data - Any data associated with the exception - may be null.
        nested - Any other nested exception - may be null.
        msgSeqNum - Message sequence number of related message - null if unknown.
        msgType - Message type of related message - null if unknown.
        tagID - Tag number of relate message field - 0 if unknown.
